{"title_page": "Goodbye (Jason Derulo and David Guetta song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Goodbye\n| cover      = GoodbyeDavidGuetta.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Jason Derulo]] and [[David Guetta]] featuring [[Nicki Minaj]] and [[Willy William]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|08|24|mf=yes}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[music streaming|streaming]]|[[contemporary hit radio]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     = \n*[[Larrabee Sound Studios|Larrabee Sound]] ([[North Hollywood]], [[California|CA]])\n*Future History ([[Los Angeles]], CA)\n*Glenwood Place ([[Burbank, California|Burbank]], CA)\n*Studio Urbain ([[Paris]], [[France]])\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Electronic Dance Music|EDM]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/hiphop/jason-derulo-nicki-minaj-goodbye-video/|title=\u00bb Nicki Minaj Completely Steals Jason Derulo\u2019s Fanciful \u2018Goodbye\u2019 Video Right From Under Him|website=Uproxx|last=Williams |first=Aaron|accessdate=3 December 2018}}</ref>|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=\"Complex\"/>}}\n| length     = 3:15\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Beluga Heights Records|Beluga Heights]]|[[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|David Guetta|Phil Greiss|[[Willy William]]| David Saint Fleur|Art Beatz|Curtis Gray|Jean-Michel Sissoko|DJ Paulito|Jazelle Rodriguez|Christopher Tempest|[[Kinnda]]|Minaj|Derulo|[[Francesco Sartori]]|[[Lucio Quarantotto]]|Franck Peterson<ref name=\"album credits\"/>}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|David Guetta|Phil Greiss|David Saint Fleur|Vodka}}\n| chronology = [[Jason Derulo]]\n| prev_title = [[Colors (Jason Derulo song)|Colors]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Make Up (Vice and Jason Derulo song)|Make Up]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[David Guetta]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Don't Leave Me Alone]]\n | prev_year  = 2018\n | title      = Goodbye\n | year       = 2018\n | next_title = Drive\n | next_year  = 2018\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Nicki Minaj]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Barbie Dreams]]\n | prev_year  = 2018\n | title      = Goodbye\n | year       = 2018\n | next_title = [[Idol (BTS song)|Idol]]\n | next_year  = 2018\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Willy William]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = Me Gusta\n | prev_year  = 2018\n | title      = Goodbye\n | year       = 2018\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|kUjKxtJd21E|\"Goodbye\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Goodbye'''\" is a song by American singer [[Jason Derulo]] and French DJ and music producer [[David Guetta]] featuring vocals from Trinidadian rapper [[Nicki Minaj]] and French recording artist [[Willy William]]. It was adapted and written by Guetta, Philippe Greiss, William, David Saint Fleur, Art Beatz, Curtis Gray, Jean-Michel Sissoko, Dj Paulito, Jazelle Rodriguez, Christopher Tempest, Kinda Ingrosso, Minaj, Derulo, [[Francesco Sartori]], [[Lucio Quarantotto]] and Franck Peterson. The latter three are credited due to the inclusion of [[Sampling (music)|elements]] of their composition \"[[Con te partir\u00f2|Time to Say Goodbye]]\", as performed by [[Sarah Brightman]] and [[Andrea Bocelli]]. \"Goodbye\" is included on Guetta's seventh studio album, ''[[7 (David Guetta album)|7]]'' (2018).\n\nThe song debuted on 23 August 2018, and was released a day later by both Guetta and Derulo's record labels \u2013 What a Music, [[Parlophone]], [[Beluga Heights Records|Beluga Heights]] and [[Warner Bros. Records]] respectively. It is the sixth single from Guetta's ''7'' album  and was unveiled alongside another single from Guetta called \"Drive\" with [[Black Coffee (DJ)|Black Coffee]] and featuring Delilah Montagu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7684774/david-guetta-nicki-minaj-jason-derulo-willy-william-goodbye-listen?|title=\u00bb Star-Studded: David Guetta, Nicki Minaj, Jason Derulo & Willy William\u2019s \"Goodbye\" Is A Banger|website=www.idolator.com}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn August 24, 2018, Guetta unveiled the sixth and seventh singles from his seventh album ''[[7 (David Guetta album)|7]]'' (2018), \"Goodbye\" and then also \"Drive\" (with [[Black Coffee (DJ)|Black Coffee]] featuring Delilah Montagu).<ref name=\"Hot101.7\">{{citeweb|url=http://www.hot1017.com/2018/08/24/listen-now-david-guetta-releases-goodbye-featuring-jason-derulo-nicki-minaj-and-willy-william/|title=Listen Now: David Guetta Releases 'Goodbye,' Featuring Jason Derulo, Nicki Minaj And Willy William|publisher=[[KHTH|101.7 FM]]|date=August 24, 2018|accessdate=September 11, 2018}}</ref> \"Goodbye\" is a collaboration with US R&B singer [[Jason Derulo]] and features Trinidadian-American rapper [[Nicki Minaj]], as well as French musician and DJ [[Willy William]]. Guetta and Minaj have previously collaborated four times, beginning in 2011 with \"[[Where Them Girls At]]\" (also featuring [[Flo Rida]]) and \"[[Turn Me On (David Guetta song)|Turn Me On]]\", both taken from Guetta's fifth album ''[[Nothing but the Beat]]''. In 2015 they collaborated on \"[[Hey Mama (David Guetta song)|Hey Mama]]\" (also featuring [[Bebe Rexha]] and [[Afrojack]]) for his sixth album ''[[Listen (David Guetta album)|Listen]]'' (2014). In 2017, they released the collaboration \"[[Light My Body Up]]\" (also featuring [[Lil Wayne]]). Meanwhile, Minaj and Derulo first collaborated in 2010 when she featured on the remix to his single \"[[In My Head (Jason Derulo song)|In My Head]]\", taken from Derulo's debut [[Jason Derulo (album)|self-titled studio album]]. They reunited in 2017 for the collaboration \"[[Swalla]]\" (also featuring [[Ty Dolla Sign|Ty Dolla $ign]]).\n\nThe song's lyric video was released alongside the song's announcement.<ref name=\"Hot101.7\"/> It features on Guetta's album ''7'' as track number six.<ref>{{cite web|title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 7 by David Guetta|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/7/1432645110|website=[[iTunes Store]]}}</ref> \"Goodbye\" samples \"[[Con te partir\u00f2|Time to Say Goodbye]]\" by Italian opera singer [[Andrea Bocelli]].<ref name=\"Complex\">{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2018/08/david-guetta-jason-derulo-willy-william-nicki-minaj-goodbye-stream|title=Listen to David Guetta and Jason Derulo's New Track \"Goodbye\" f/ Nicki Minaj and Willy William|work=Complex|date=August 24, 2018|accessdate=September 11, 2018}}</ref> The official music video was released on October 21, 2018.\n\n== Live performances ==\nGuetta, Derulo and Minaj performed the song at the [[2018 MTV Europe Music Awards]].\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits adapted from album booklet.<ref name=\"album credits\">{{citeweb|url=http://davidguetta.com/7-thealbum/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180915192715/http://davidguetta.com/7-thealbum/|url-status=dead|archive-date=15 September 2018|title=''7'' \u2014 David Guetta|publisher=What A Music / [[Parlophone Records]] ([[Warner Music|Warner France]])|accessdate=15 September 2018|date=14 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n*David Saint Fleur \u2013 [[Record producer|producer]]\n*David Guetta \u2013 producer, [[disc jockey|DJ]]\n*Vodka \u2013 producer\n*Phil Greiss \u2013 producer, engineer, keyboards, masterer, mixer, recording\n*Kat Dahlia \u2013 background vocals\n*Jazelle \"JVZEL\" Rodriguez \u2013 background vocals\n*Ludovic Mullor \u2013 engineer\n*Ben Hogarth \u2013 engineer\n*Aubry \"Big Juice\" Delaine \u2013 engineer\n*Luca Pretolesi \u2013 mastering, mixing\n*Jason Derulo \u2013 vocals\n*Nicki Minaj \u2013 vocals\n*Willy William \u2013 vocals\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|33|artist=Jason Derulo x David Guetta feat. Nicki Minaj And Willy William|song=Goodbye|rowheader=tru