ctive Experience'', Chap. 2. Mitch Earlywine, ed. Oxford University Press.\n* MirAhmadi, As Sayed Nurjan (2005) ''Healing Power of Sufi Meditation''. Islamic Supreme Council of America.\n* Nirmalananda Giri, Swami (2007) [https://web.archive.org/web/20090717100414/http://www.spiritualnow.com/blogs/112/Om-Meditation-Its-Theory-and-Practice.html Om Yoga: Its Theory and Practice] In-depth study of the classical meditation method of the Bhagavad Gita, Yoga Sutras of Patanjali, and the Upanishads.\n* {{Cite journal |author1=Ospina Maria B. |author2=Kenneth Bond |author3=Mohammad Karkhaneh |author4=Lisa Tjosvold |author5=Ben Vandermeer |author6=Yuanyuan Liang |author7=Liza Bialy |author8=Nicola Hooton |author9=Nina Buscemi |author10=Donna M. Dryden |author11=Terry P. Klassen |title=Meditation practices for health: state of the research |journal=Evidence Report / Technology Assessment (Full Report), Prepared by the University of Alberta Evidence-based Practice Center Under Contract No. 290-02-0023) |issue=155 |pages=1\u2013263 |date=June 2007 |pmid=17764203 |url=http://www.ahrq.gov/downloads/pub/evidence/pdf/meditation/medit.pdf |pmc=4780968 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090225175425/http://www.ahrq.gov/downloads/pub/evidence/pdf/meditation/medit.pdf |archivedate=2009-02-25 |df=}}\n* {{cite journal | last1=Perez-De-Albeniz | first1=Alberto | last2=Holmes | first2=Jeremy | year=2000 | title=Meditation: Concepts, Effects And Uses In Therapy | journal=International Journal of Psychotherapy | volume=5 | issue=1| pages=49\u201358 | doi=10.1080/13569080050020263}}\n* Shalif, Ilan et al. (1989) [https://web.archive.org/web/20080822052515/http://www.etext.org/Psychology/Shalif/emotions ''Focusing on the Emotions of Daily Life''] (Tel-Aviv: Etext Archives, 2008)\n* {{cite journal |doi=10.1176/ajp.139.3.267 |pmid=7036760 |title=Overview: Clinical and physiological comparison of meditation with other self-control strategies |journal=American Journal of Ps